<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7031149>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Cladosporium pseudotenuissimum (VIC 44422, holotype). A–D. Colonies on A. Potato dextrose agar; B. Malt extract agar; C. Oatmeal agar; D. Synthetic nutrient-poor agar, after 14 days at 25 ºC, under near-ultraviolet light, respectively. E–J. Macronematous conidiophores and conidia. E, F. Micronematous conidiophores at arrows. K. Conidiogenous cel with conidia. L. Bubble-like swelling details. M. Microcyclic conidiogenesis (black arrow) and Ramoconidia (red arrow). Scale bars: E = 50 µM; F–M = 20 µM." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7031149/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

